The paper deals with the problem of obtaining an antisparse representation, which is relevant in several areas of computer science such as digital communication and machine learning. The proposed methodology involves solving a convex program with an $\ell_\infty$-norm penalty combined with a quadratic discrepancy. This suggests that the paper could belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT), Machine Learning (cs.LG), Signal Processing (cs.SP), Numerical Analysis (cs.NA), or Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-categories.
